# Sprint Debugger Enhancements

Implement 4 features: smart sprint filter, improved personnel view sorting, structured daily meeting notes in the task inspector, and a context documentation file.

## Proposed Changes

### Feature 1 — Smart Sprint Filter

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/page.tsx)

Replace the hardcoded sprint `<select>` dropdown with a **sprint configuration system**:

- Define a `SPRINT_CONFIG` array with sprint number, start date, and end date
- Auto-detect the current sprint based on `Date.now()` falling within a sprint's date range
- Default `selectedSprint` state to the current sprint number instead of `''` (all sprints)
- Show the active sprint's date range label in the header (e.g., "Sprint 10 · Mar 3 – Mar 14")

---

### Feature 2 — Personnel View Sorting

#### [MODIFY] [PersonnelOverview.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/PersonnelOverview.tsx)

- Sort tasks **within each person card** using a priority-weighted sort:
  1. **Status priority**: Reprocess (1) > Waiting to Integrate (2) > In Process (3) > Not Started (4) > *(others)* (5) > Staging Passed (6)
  2. **Stale hours** (descending, as secondary sort key)
- Display stale duration prominently on each task row
- Add a small status-priority indicator color dot next to each task for scanability

#### [MODIFY] [workflow-engine.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/workflow-engine.ts)

- Sort person summaries by: most stale hours total (desc), then by count of critical-status tasks (desc)

---

### Feature 3 — Enhanced Task Inspector with Meeting Notes

#### [MODIFY] [types.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/types.ts)

Add a new `MeetingNote` interface:
```ts
interface MeetingNote {
  id: string;
  taskId: string;
  date: string;       // ISO date string  
  isStall: boolean;
  stallReason: string;
  blockedBy: string;   // person name
  solution: string;
  createdAt: string;   // ISO timestamp
}
```

#### [NEW] [useMeetingNotes.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/hooks/useMeetingNotes.ts)

New hook for localStorage-persisted meeting notes, keyed by `taskId`. Methods:
- `addNote(note: MeetingNote)` — persist a new note
- `getNotesForTask(taskId: string): MeetingNote[]` — retrieve all notes for a task
- `getAllNotes(): Record<string, MeetingNote[]>` — all notes across tasks

#### [MODIFY] [StandupInspector.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/inspector/StandupInspector.tsx)

Major redesign of the side panel:

1. **All Assigned People section** — show all unique people from the task's `statusHistory` (derived from [TaskAnalysis](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/lib/types.ts#68-84)) as avatar-like badges at the top
2. **"+ Add Today's Meeting Note" button** — opens an inline form:
   - Toggle: "Is this task stalled?" → shows stall reason textarea
   - "Blocked by" dropdown: auto-populated with all assigned people on this task + team leaders (Bùi Anh Đức, Phạm Đức Toàn)
   - "Solution" textarea
   - Save button
3. **Meeting Note Timeline** — below the form, show all saved meeting notes for this task in reverse chronological order. Each note card shows:
   - Date (prominent, e.g., "Thu, Mar 6")
   - Stall indicator (red badge if stalled)
   - "Blocked by: [name]"
   - Solution text
   - Timestamp

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/app/page.tsx)

- Wire the new `useMeetingNotes` hook
- Pass meeting notes data + handlers to [StandupInspector](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/inspector/StandupInspector.tsx#34-308)

---

### Feature 4 — Context Documentation

#### [NEW] [CONTEXT.md](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/CONTEXT.md)

A reference document covering:
- **Workflow Statuses**: each status name, description, and whether it's a bottleneck
- **Terminologies**: Doom Loop, Bottleneck, Stale Task, Reprocess, Risk Levels
- **Team Structure**: Team leaders (Bùi Anh Đức, Phạm Đức Toàn) and member roles
- **Sprint Structure**: Sprint numbering and duration conventions

---

## Verification Plan

### Browser Verification
1. Run `npm run dev` (already running) and open the app
2. Verify the sprint filter defaults to the current sprint and shows the date range
3. Switch between sprints to confirm filtering works
4. Go to Personnel tab — confirm tasks are sorted by status priority then stale hours
5. Click a task — verify the inspector shows all assigned people
6. Use the "Add Today's Meeting Note" form — verify the blocked-by dropdown includes task assignees + leaders
7. Save a note, refresh the page, and verify persistence
8. Check the meeting note timeline displays chronologically with readable formatting

### Build Check
- Run `npm run build` to ensure no TypeScript errors
